Bootstrap: localimage
From: ./ubuntu_22.04.sif

%post
    set -e

    # Update APT index and install required packages
    apt-get update -y
    DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        python3-pip \
        jq \
        ca-certificates \
        && apt-get clean && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

    # Install pytest for the exercise test-harness
    python3 -m pip install --no-cache-dir --upgrade pip
    python3 -m pip install --no-cache-dir pytest

    # ------------------------------------------------------------------
    # Create initial filesystem state for the IoT connection report task
    # ------------------------------------------------------------------
    mkdir -p /home/user/edge_devices/reports

    cat > /home/user/edge_devices/devices.json <<'EOF'
[
  {"id":"sensor-1","ip":"10.0.0.11","status":"online"},
  {"id":"sensor-2","ip":"10.0.0.12","status":"offline"},
  {"id":"gateway-1","ip":"10.0.0.1","status":"online"},
  {"id":"camera-1","ip":"10.0.0.20","status":"offline"},
  {"id":"sensor-3","ip":"10.0.0.13","status":"online"}
]
EOF

    # Ensure the reports directory is writable by the unprivileged user
    chmod 0777 /home/user/edge_devices/reports

%labels
    chmod 755 /home/user

    Author IoT-Edge Exercise Generator
    Description Container for the “IoT connection report” task. Includes pytest and provides the required initial filesystem state.

%help
This container sets up the starting environment for the “IoT connection report” exercise.

 directory layout:
   /home/user/edge_devices/
       ├─ devices.json     (initial inventory)
       └─ reports/         (empty, writable; student writes report here)

The container also has pytest pre-installed for automated grading.